    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 2g: TMUB1 and GluR2 (GRIA2) were both enriched in synaptosomal membrane fractions and had a similar enrichment pattern over various biochemical fractions prepared from mouse brains.\n\nFigure 2b: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for TMUB1 and PSD-95 (DLG4) in cultured hippocampal rat neurons showed partial co-localization.\n\nFigure 7: A large portion of Tmub1/HOPS colocalizes with GluR2 at recycling endosomes.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: Results, Figure 2 legend: \"(A) Double immunostaining of Tmub1/HOPS along with the dendritic marker MAP2 using cultured rat hippocampal neurons.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"For the production of the rabbit polyclonal antibody for Tmub1/HOPS, a fusion protein containing 29-191 aa of Tmub1/HOPS attached to a GST tag at the N terminus was purified on a GST column and used as an antigen. The antibody was purified by affinity chromatography using a HiTrap NHS-activated column (GE Healthcare, Uppsala, Sweden) coupled with maltose-binding protein-Tmub1/HOPS fusion proteins. \"",
